  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Sinus is formed by penetration of skin by ingrowing hair\nLeads to foreign body granuloma reaction, sinus perpetuated by repeated bouts of infection\nCarcinoma is rare complication of chronic, recurring pilonidal sinus disease",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "May present as a painless cyst, acute\nabscess\n, or recurring cysts with draining sinuses\nOccurs in midline in the upper part of the natal cleft\nDoes not communicate with the anorectum\nBecause of proximity to anus can be confused for a perianal abscess",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
